The Joy of Touring Season 1

Travel Documentary hosted by Elisa Schwartz, published by Discovery Channel in 2013 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

It is often said that an organized tour is one of the most pleasant and safest way to travel. Whether cruising in Vietnam, hot air ballooning in Turkey, joining a South African photo safari, there are many experiences showcased in this series. Viewers visit mythical places, explore history and take on new challenges while discovering some of the world's most beautiful destinations.


1)  Southwestern USA 
The American West is featured in the premiere of this series, which highlights the most beautiful places in the world.

2)  Thailand 
The jungles of Thailand are explored.

3)  Vietnam 
Highlighting the wonders of Vietnam

4)  Tunisia 
A look at what Tunisia has to offer visitors

5)  Corsica 
Exploring the culture, traditions and history of Corsica, the French island in the heart of the Mediterranean Sea.

6)  Equador 
Interesting facts about Ecuador are picked up during a tour of the country

7)  Italy 
A tour of Italy includes the country's art, history and food.

8)  South Africa 
Famous landmarks, tourist attractions and places to visit in South Africa. Included: the colorful countryside; Kruger National Park; the cities of Cape Town and Soweto.

9)  Spain and Portugal 
The early explorations of Spain and Portugal are examined as the countries are toured.

10)  Turkey 
The culture and history of Turkey are explored during a tour of the country

11)  Ireland 
Traveling through Ireland. Included: the Emerald Isle's rolling green landscapes, castles and pubs, plus a distillery tour.

12)  Rocky Mountains 
Touring the Canadian Rockies, from Calgary to Victoria. Included: a Rocky Mountaineer train trip

13)  Bolivia and Peru 
Exploring the historical, natural and cultural attractions of these two south American countries

